 Because the (money made/good thing received) described in Eq. (1) is watched/followed only for 
 the chosen species, one must correct for possible selection bias 
 when guessing the (may or may not happen, depending on something) net money/money income or numbers of 
 animals (Heckman, 1979). Since the farmer (makes as big as possible) net money/money income (may or may not happen, depending on something) on the choice of that species, the error in the 
 second-stage equation may be related to the error in the 
 first stage. According to Dubin and McFadden (1984), with the 
 idea (you think is true) of the following (being like a line) condition 4 : 
