 5. Climate tests 
 We now test out the results of climate change using 
 the limit/guideline guesses from the previous section. We examine a set of climate change pictures/situations (described the future) by Air-related 
 Ocean-related General Circulation Models (AOGCMs). The climate 
 pictures/situations reflect the A2 SRES pictures/situations from the following 
 three models: the Canadian Climate Center (CCC) picture/situation 
 (Boer et al., 2000), Center for Climate System Research (CCSR) 
 (Emori et al., 1999), and Parallel Climate Model (PCM) (Washington et al., 2003). The models were selected to provide a range 
 of climate pictures/situations from mild (PCM) to extreme (CCC). For each 
 model, we examine country-level climate change pictures/situations in 
 2020, 2060, and 2100. For each climate picture/situation, we added 
